commit_message:
Exception wrapper to handle type errors

If an invalid metric type makes it through StatsD we can handle
it more gracefully by logging the type error instead of producing
a stack dump.

Change-Id: I05c0042d9132efc2a856db43923873f1f6bcb3d2

commit_message:
Fix in-place operation on reset values

If a value is reset on flush(), it will subsequently fail
on sample().  This seems to affect a subset of statsd metrics,
filling the log with "Error receiving datagram" messages.

This patch also fixes a couple very minor PEP8 issues.

Change-Id: I7dfb3b62fcf110ba7dd0ef2d3e6f40ee7c1891ef

commit_message:
Prevent scheduling new external events when compute is shutdown

During graceful shutdown, we should make sure that any threads that
we are waiting for completion don't try to schedule new events after
we have canceled all the inflight ones.

This patch should ensure that:

1. We don't wait on those
2. We fast-fail with typical error behavior
3. We still run the code they're expecting to run

Change-Id: I5ac47935a9ef841000f0a8954d78a4a98644844e
Closes-Bug: #1438183

commit_message:
get_items on non-existent collection

Querying non-existent policy or datasource returns empty list,
Whereas it should return http 404 (Not Found).

Change-Id: Iac8931b46eff526e050d982966a10098dcd07d30
Closes-Bug: #1359448

commit_message:
Rearrange hypervisors response schemas into one file

After removing v3 schemas, we have only 1 set of schemas for v2 (/v2.1)
APIs but those end up in scattered structure.

Schema files needs to be re arranged into a clean structure. Any
resource schema should be defined in single file for better readability.

This patch rearrange hypervisors response schema into one file and merge some
of common schema definition.

Partially implements blueprint rearrange-nova-response-schemas

Change-Id: I21b90b8410ea62a94f8f41ecf714e2158015c6d2

commit_message:
Do not write a localrc

Append to local.conf instead. The devstack documentation
asks the user to put congress in the list of enabled
services. Adding a localrc makes devstack ignore
local.conf, leading to some services being not installed.

Change-Id: If07cf5944db8813dea26862e889dca1deb247d83

state in the server always matches the database content because there
can be just one Congress server modifying the database.  With the
basic high-availability solution, one congress server replica can
modify the database without a second replica knowing, so the running
state of the datasources can become out of sync with the database.

The new version of the datasource status API call returns the status
of the datasource if the datasource is running in the server, even if
the database does not contain the datasource.

This change also makes the list-datasources API call update the
running datasources to match the database after fetching the
datasource configuration from the database.

This also adds a tempest test to verify that datasource
synchronization works.

Implements blueprint: basic-high-availability

commit_message:
Add datasource synchronizer

The datasource synchronizer reads from the configuration database on a
periodic basis and checks whether the active datasources match the
configuration in the database.  If the two do to match, the
synchronizer changes the active datasources to match the database.

By default, datasource synchronization is off.  To enable it, add a
line like this
   datasource_sync_period = 60
to the congress.conf configuration file.

This change includes a change to the datasource status API semantics.
The previous version of the status handler first checks that the
datasource exists in the database; if the datasource does not the
handler responds to the client with and error because the running
state in the server always matches the database content because there
can be just one Congress server modifying the database.  With the
basic high-availability solution, one congress server replica can
modify the database without a second replica knowing, so the running
state of the datasources can become out of sync with the database.

The new version of the datasource status API call returns the status
of the datasource if the datasource is running in the server, even if
the database does not contain the datasource.

This change also makes the list-datasources API call update the
running datasources to match the database after fetching the
datasource configuration from the database.

This also adds a tempest test to verify that datasource
synchronization works.

Implements blueprint: basic-high-availability
Change-Id: I732c965c616f0f11d4d30f7f90b0cce980f9342d

commit_message:
Export image properties

Some elements (such as the manifests element) want to use these
variables. We currently do not consistently export them (IMAGE_NAME is
only exported if you actually specify a name).

Change-Id: I43d17ddcdd7d0ff3cbb4c530caeebb8da915f4ef

commit_message:
Clone requirements repository before setting up DB

Setting up the database requires the global requirements file which is in the
requirements repository. If that repository is not cloned the requirements file
does not exist and so installing the database fails. With this change the
requirements repository is cloned before setting up the database.

Change-Id: Ie06e02acf72429b65596bc5a64e86a6dd630f0ee
Closes-Bug: #1441816

commit_message:
Add support to skip either kernel or ramdisk

Currently, glance.create_or_find_kernel_and_ramdisk() will raise an
exception if either the kernel or ramdisk are not found in Glance.
This makes it fairly awkward for others to use the API if they need
to deal with a missing kernel, but an existing ramdisk since the
function will never check, because the exception is raised when the
kernel isn't found.

Change-Id: I872a080846c7a191039e89afaa587cafbd853fe4

commit_message:
Update customizing docs to include themes

Themes for horizon were recently introducted in
https://review.openstack.org/#/c/159300/. This
change updates the documentation on customizing
to include themes.

Change-Id: I48d04008a44e4ac7efe46d3ec3fbbdc15a55258b
Closes-bug: #1435384

commit_message:
Allows selection of floating IP pool in Javelin

javelin2 doesn't allow selection of a floating-ip pool which are a
necessity to use Javelin on multi-host environments.

This patch allows to add this from the resource definition yaml file.

Change-Id: Ifdb84dc1e8a220dec18fc043e4175d3855b0677f

commit_message:
Fix bad performance on project update panel

Modify the Edit Project action use get_project_user_roles API
instead of making a separate call for each user.

The get_project_user_roles API which enables this improvement
is new in Keystone V3. Improved performance will be seen only
when using Keystone V3.

Change-Id: I204f25800abcbc35a130d351431c938b01c72d18

commit_message:
Skip test_volume_boot_pattern until bug 1439371 is fixed

The check-tempest-dsvm-full-ceph job sets volume.storage_protocol to
'ceph' in devstack-gate and the test is failing with a ceph backend, so
skip it while that's being debugged.

The plan is to get the ceph job passing consistently so we can make it
voting on nova/cinder/glance changes so we can tell when a change
regresses it.

Related-Bug: #1439371

Change-Id: Ia1cba598a8243dd4a48613c870a25de578b79fe4

commit_message:
Fix fixed_network bug 1439634 - ipsec issue

fixed_networks only verified if tenant isolation is enabled
that does not account for the case of force tenant isolation,
where an isolated tenant will be available regardless of the
tenant isolation default setting.

Closes-bug: #1439634
Change-Id: Id1743ac18b6b52a3ee6bb533a7a348432ce1f466

commit_message:
Move elasticsearch dep to test-requirements.txt

Move experimental feature deps to test-requirements Optional and experimental
features should not make glance dependant on the libraries they require. This
change moves the python bindings for elasticsearch from the main
requirements.txt to test-requirements.txt.

semantic_version should potentially also be moved here, but it is currently
required to do a db sync and is generally less alarming than an elasticsearch
dependency. It is instead moved to the bottom of requirements.txt and marked as
being artifacts related.

Co-Authored-By: Matt Riedemann <mriedem@us.ibm.com>

Change-Id: I7f8dfafdb11dbf7ba258e907fbd17d92319d0f52
Closes-bug: #1441239

commit_message:
Update openstack-common reference in openstack/common/README

The README file under the openstack/common directory references to
openstack-common, but the link points to oslo-incubator (which is
correct). Update the file, so it use oslo-incubator instead of
openstack-common.

Change-Id: I0a8e9beb43a0296bd5d1c94460a3e7e0e685138b
Closes-Bug: 1434370

commit_message:
Fixed NotificationTransformer to handle missing InstanceServiceStatus

Fixed NotificationTransformer to not send exists notifications for
new Trove instances which do not have an InstanceServiceStatus
created for them yet. The notifications for these instances will
eventually be sent during the next iteration of the scheduled task.

Change-Id: I002ab89f8c7715310f1890a34967c8172a5d96ef
Closes-Bug: 1379729
(cherry picked from commit 80f898d3ba16d5c644447dbacf3a1bad6eaa6488)

commit_message:
Added tenant impersonation to API

* Added 2 new HTTP Headers
** X-Auth-Sudo-Tenant-ID
** X-Auth-Sudo-Project-ID

These are mutually exclusive, but will change the tenant in designate
to the provided values, if the calling user has the correct permissions
in the policy (defaults to rule:admin)

* Always attach the context to the request, even if the policy check
fails

Change-Id: I8f55390cf8ff45fa8999b5a0239639cf862f7789
Closes-Bug: #1441286

commit_message:
Return container not found before ACL checks

This fixes a recent regression where one user would get a 403 when
trying to retrieve a unknown container, instead of a 404.

Change-Id: I59c6b806591ca4c943615c3b528752ef8ba1e0dd
Closes-Bug: #1441555

"}]
commit_message:
compute: don't trace on InstanceNotFound in reverts_task_state

Commit c43f2b0d708f0f4b37850d2917c0abcc13b8789b added logging when
_instance_update fails in reverts_task_state but we shouldn't log
InstanceNotFound since it's a normal (expected) error when we're
deleting an instance shortly after it fails to build.

Closes-Bug: #1431404

NOTE(mriedem): The test uses instance_obj.Instance rather than
objects.Instance since nova.objects isn't imported in the test
module in stable/icehouse.

Change-Id: Iec3dfaa16b472bc88d56d9c6680a7c247f2f50bd
(cherry picked from commit 95976ca1aff63c01ed119c9a3c39927f39ce1fbf)
(cherry picked from commit 5ff5afe7df8e296f03fd9fd86ad169360cc91451)

commit_message:
Fix exception handling in Glance image service

At the moment there is literally no exception handling in
glance_service.base_image_service, as it tries to catch Ironic
exceptions instead of Glance client exceptions. This change fixes
this behaviour.

Change-Id: Iaaeb234c68088538534f2a455f3678079cc60145
Closes-bug: #1441727

commit_message:
add ceilometermiddleware to requirements

ceilometer uses ceilometermiddleware to pull metrics via api. this
patch adds it to global reqs.

Change-Id: I8a5c330cf9f3b1b08bc1dd084c9a1461016b855c
Closes-Bug: #1441655

commit_message:
Adding configuration instructions in huawei_nas_driver.rst

add - `driver_handles_share_servers` = False
add 'As far as Manila requires `share type` for creation of
shares, make sure that used `share type` has extra spec
`driver_handles_share_servers` set to `False` otherwise Huawei
back end will be filtered by `manila-scheduler`.'

Change-Id: Ic031e28a0691fb05a99c33b1569558cfb2cc4609
Closes-Bug: #1440946

commit_message:
Add vscsi disconnect volume support

Provide support for vscsi disconnect volume which will remove the
physical volume mapping and delete the hdisk if the conf setting
is enabled.

commit_message:
Update proliantutils version required for K release

This commit updates the proliantutils version
required in Ironic to 2.1.0 for K release.  This 
version of proliantutils includes the following 
functionality:
* Enablement of RIS protocol for Proliant Gen9 
  servers on which uefi secure boot feature depends.
* Functionality for node inspection using *ilo drivers.
* Functionality for node cleaning.

Change-Id: I09db1eca7fb6d383edaeac5da909d9bb84a8a009

commit_message:
Fix mocks not being stopped as intended

Mock objects were being created that were intended to be started and
stopped.  But they were not actually being stopped.  Fix it so they are
being stopped correctly, add autospec=True to the mock objects, and
update some side_effects to work with autospec=True.

Change-Id: I4ced8eb8a4fe874405f0b53132a38e276eef01b5

commit_message:
Encode x-auth-token in http header

X-auth-token in http header is not encoded currently. Need to
encode it in order to ensure httplib call will not break. It is
a Python 2 problem only.

Change-Id: Ic780693751175c3c1e21f50777dc5a02f3eb7a8c
Closes-Bug: 1387327

commit_message:
[Launch Instance fix] Show header for Source Allocated table

For consistency with the mockups, we show the table headers
for the Allocated transfer tables, even when initially empty.

Change-Id: I08dd20f1da13d373addcf409738f4dc9a40e5f07
Closes-Bug: #1436931

commit_message:
Updated parsing of catalog to handle bad format

Don't assume that the service catalog is well-formed, added code
to safely parsing the catalog.

Parsing of region from service catalog has been fixed as well.
'region' has been deprecated in the Keystone V3 catalog in favor of
'region_id'. Fix how region is extracted by checking 'region_id' then
fallback to 'region'.

Change-Id: I7b649a8b90e20caa2d04fdd3f79b5b1ac775237c
Closes-Bug: #1424825

commit_message:
Just unify having a single requirements.txt file

The difference between the py2 and py3 requirements file
is marginal and it does not harm py3 from having additional
dependencies that aren't used anyway so just have a single
requirements file.

Change-Id: I969ea61f68a2c7c2d7fb4d38e6e1d3daa59b0d40

commit_message:
[Launch Instance Fix] Add Network Step Unit Tests

This patch adds unit tests for the network steps.  These tests are focused
around the controller and its related components (no selenium tests or view
tests).

Change-Id: I0f4b0ef900e5f17c7b39e9f3ca60780e0d26b8e8
Partial-Bug: 1435869

commit_message:
Fix NeutronLoadBalancerTest.test_neutron_loadbalancer timeout

NeutronLoadBalancerTest.test_neutron_loadbalancer timeout
happens occasionally. Added WaitCondition resource to
signal back after SimpleHTTPServer is started.

Change-Id: I73085d1b20277fba9f28460abaa991d489d2447a
Closes-Bug: #1437203

commit_message:
introduce pip_install_gr

This creates a new pip_install_gr that installs from global
requirements allowed versions. Now that stable branches are getting
capped all of devstack needs to be fixed to do things like this.

Change-Id: I8fd0ef2bfc544ca2576fab09d3018f760b8848fe

commit_message:
Make Image Type translatable

On the image tables the Type values are not translatable.
Update the code so they can be translated.

Change-Id: Ibde03a5e2281fad80ecc21e56e8b92bbe432c368
Closes-Bug: 1441196

commit_message:
xenapi: pull vm_mode and auto_disk_config from image when rescue.

Updating vmops.py to pull vm_mode and auto_disk_config from the image
during rescue mode to ensure the vm is properly built based on the image
properties in the image_meta dictionary.

Change-Id: I29c89e9a17f9a170dbe61e4fe14672d481c4fb78
Closes-Bug: 1432913

commit_message:
Reflect the fact that devstack takes 10-15 minutes now

With all the assorted devstack configurations and plugins, it rarely
takes 5 minutes and commonly takes over 15 minutes.

* Update logs to reflect how long we expect this to take
* Bump the devstack is slow warning to 20 minutes.

Change-Id: I89971ac07c978cc1a40b0178931f8cc2663f323b

commit_message:
Remove filter for tasks to show logs for all actions

This patch removes filters which prevent showing logs for actions.
As actions are called automatically by Ceilometer or other 3rd party tool,
a user has no chance to see actions task logs rather than checking deployment
history logs.

Change-Id: Ia3b4240f4b2bb8463acd65bd299aa0d0cc3fc6e9
Closes-Bug: #1369781

Change-Id: I82ccddd1dee87fc6153476419ca15309b7cc9529

commit_message:
Fix regex for excluding slow tests in Nova Cells V1 job

There is a bug in the current regex for excluding slow tests.
Instead of excluding the slow tests, it is excluding every test
except the slow tests -- the inverse of what we want.

Change-Id: I82ccddd1dee87fc6153476419ca15309b7cc9529

commit_message:
Added NPM executions for StoryBoard Tests.

The first npm-based job has successfully completed. These
tests enable three additional jobs which add a new layer of
complexity, namely the use of the xvfb to run firefox and
chromium tests.

Depends-on: 990f2c7d84725e02b25f4a37c70679406410e48b

commit_message:
Add shared storage driver methods

Add the shared storage methods to the compute driver for the
SSP disk driver. The methods are used a part of the resize
and evacuate instance operations.

Change-Id: I8d2eb50ce467da143c44a8713b934a4aa96b78aa

commit_message:
Remove str() casting for the client_message variable

This is done since the e.client_message variable is a unicode
string that might be derived from a non-ascii input (for
example, the user-supplied paylaod content type). If the str()
function is applied to a non-ascii char, a UnicodeEncodeError
exception will be thrown.

Change-Id: I3ce5454a37347297b3ec0b0124234025a4aed872
Closes-bug: #1435613
Related-Bug: #1421478

commit_message:
introduce pip_install_gr

This creates a new pip_install_gr that installs from global
requirements allowed versions. Now that stable branches are getting
capped all of devstack needs to be fixed to do things like this.

Conflicts:
	inc/python
	lib/ceilometer
	lib/databases/mysql
	lib/databases/postgresql
	lib/horizon
	lib/keystone
	lib/ldap
	lib/nova_plugins/functions-libvirt
	lib/nova_plugins/hypervisor-xenserver
	lib/tempest
	lib/zaqar
	pkg/elasticsearch.sh
	stack.sh

Change-Id: I8fd0ef2bfc544ca2576fab09d3018f760b8848fe
(cherry picked from commit 19e06206cd66713d3f776baaefc050a965edc037)

commit_message:
updated dev requirements to allow for linting python

The python files within the stack are not able to pass lint checks
using the same standard which OpenStack requires. This change adds
the requirements to the dev-requirements.txt file which will enable
hacking/flake8 checks within our stack.

These requirements mirror what is presently found within upstream
OpenStack global requirements.

Partial-Bug: 1440462

revisions:
[{'created': '2015-04-03 09:32:54.000000000', 'message': 'Allow libvirt secret key setting from param

Currently the libvirt secret key is demanded to the ceph cluster
via the $(ceph auth get-key ...) command which requires the ceph
cluste to be already up and also assumes the computes are provisioned
with the client.admin keyring.

With this change we add a libvirt_rbd_secret_key parameter which,
if passed, is used instead so that computes can be configured
without the distribution of additional keys.

Change-Id: I70da06159c0d3c6fa204b5f7a468909ffab4d633
Closes-Bug: #1439949
'}, {'created': '2015-04-03 09:36:54.000000000', 'message': 'Allow libvirt secret key setting from param

commit_message:
Allow libvirt secret key setting from param

Currently the libvirt secret key is demanded to the ceph cluster
via the $(ceph auth get-key ...) command which requires the ceph
cluste to be already up and also assumes the computes are provisioned
with the client.admin keyring.

With this change we add a libvirt_rbd_secret_key parameter which,
if passed, is used instead so that computes can be configured
without the distribution of additional keys.

Change-Id: I70da06159c0d3c6fa204b5f7a468909ffab4d633
Closes-Bug: #1439949

commit_message:
Specify that argparse is only required for Python < 2.7

In Python 2.6, argparse was not part of the standard library. However,
as of Python 2.7 / 3.2, argparse is part of the standard library and
does not need to be named as a dependency.

- New in version 2.7: https://docs.python.org/2/library/argparse.html
- New in version 3.2: https://docs.python.org/3/library/argparse.html

This patch uses environment markers as implemented in pip 6.0:
https://github.com/dstufft/pip/commit/e498d83db191ccd7fe7c1c2e4f9ec201787d1257

Change-Id: Iabc1779cf0e6e347d58da739946d3ea91482caa1
Closes-Bug: 1441083

commit_message:
Moved sleep in Nailgun agent

Node should not wait after checking '/var/run/nodiscover' file
when reboot is started, it should give Astute time to react
(and to create this file) and only then check it and reboot.

Change-Id: I2c6464262e100244bc525f8e8b456eb26d35e3a1
Related-Bug: #1371225

commit_message:
Pin version of python-ironicclient pulled from pip to be inline with GR

python-ironicclient is left out of nova's requirements.txt intentionally,
meaning we can't rely on g-r's version constraints to keep things working.
We have to instead manually specify them to pip here, according to versions
set in stable/juno's g-r.txt

Change-Id: I16482097111ee75058579c25151abd6178d90f13
Closes-bug: #1441376
Related-bug: #1441374

commit_message:
[IBP] fix scary udev errors

Udev was moaning about its zero-sized rule files.
Adding a simple empty rule will help to avoid all error messages
such as 'udevd: can not read'.

Change-Id: I7777e1e1f17491cdc3aa91d538c23e0c5a4ab849

commit_message:
Port to Python 3

* added python 3.3 and 3.4 to the setup
* fixed job binaries test to use proper byte object

Change-Id: I61aaf435f28ebb30141878137921056bc9025e18
Implements: blueprint python3-compatible

commit_message:
Don't run check-tempest-dsvm-full-ceph job on stable icehouse/juno

Bug 1399244 still exists on the stable branches so restrict the ceph job
from running on stable/icehouse and stable/juno.

This is the first step in making the job voting on master for nova and
cinder.

Related-Bug: #1439371

Change-Id: Iac44c6a84a39a518f4800483558bbe5223a41359

commit_message:
Parse api errors during package and bundle uploads

Before only a generic error message would be shown in case an error
occurred during package upload.
Adds a common method to parse api v1 webob-based errors and handles
errors during package/bundle upload

Change-Id: I1f12ecfb7b7577d3d87c17848f7f5a1d87ff57dc
Closes-Bug: #1441706

[{'created': '2015-04-06 16:44:35.000000000', 'message': "[IBP] Add udevadm trigger

As far as we're doing udev rules blacklisting during disk
partitioning, we need to call 'udevadm trigger' after all paritioning
will be done in order to re-create all the links which were skipped by
udev while blacklisted.

Since udev is async, we need to use 'udevadm settle' to be synced with
udev workers.

Related-Bug: #1410471
Change-Id: I7bb8be57de699fffe5f96ef6fe3112cf5f2b5a20
"}]
commit_message:
[IBP] Add udevadm trigger

As far as we're doing udev rules blacklisting during disk
partitioning, we need to call 'udevadm trigger' after all paritioning
will be done in order to re-create all the links which were skipped by
udev while blacklisted.

Since udev is async, we need to use 'udevadm settle' to be synced with
udev workers.

Related-Bug: #1410471
Change-Id: I7bb8be57de699fffe5f96ef6fe3112cf5f2b5a20

commit_message:
IBP: improve exception handling in fuel-agent

This patch resolves the issue with exception's message carrying and
adds very high level try/except clause to fuel-agent entrypoint.

Closes-Bug: #1422448

commit_message:
Describes nova-compute-vCenter mapping

* Remove limitation about 1-1 mapping in Planning Guide
* Add description and scheme into Operations Guide

Change-Id: If2936189068c0826a98e9caa264827baab554933
Implements: blueprint 1-1-nova-compute-vsphere-cluster-mapping
Closes-Bug: 1403928

commit_message:
Add Application Catalog project into Stackforge

apps-catalog is a front-end for Glance images, Heat templates and
Murano applications. To be hosted on catalog.openstack.org

Change-Id: Ifd8e6c30ae1981503bf06103e09d0d4e71b6ef45

boot_mode is overwritten in node properties

iLO drivers overwrite boot_mode in the node's properties/capabilities
when UEFI secure boot is requested.

Closes-Bug: 1436791

commit_message:
Make block device mapping timeout configurable

When booting instances passing in block-device and increasing the
volume size, instances can go in to error state if the volume takes
longer to create than 3 minutes (current default value).

This change adds support for 2 new cluster configutation options:
- block_device_allocate_retries (default: 300)
- block_device_allocate_retries_interval (default: 3)

Thess options are configurable via fuel cli or Hiera. They are added
to nova.conf on compute nodes and allow to adjust block device
allocation timeout value.

DocImpact

Change-Id: If9148da046d31aab60a13bd70e94700331770000
Closes-bug: #1280399

commit_message:
Adds information about dual hypervisor support

Since Fuel 6.1 provides dual hypervisor support
with availability zones, these changes should be
reflected in User Guide.

Change-Id: I97fea5aeb958119881b63646b4de4b25843330a9
Implements: blueprint vmware-dual-hypervisor
Closes-Bug: 1427679
Closes-Bug: 1426381

commit_message:
Update path for listing a project's endpoint groups

The original route didn't exist in any version of keystone yet,
so the API was broken in that regard. Also, it should be changed
to be more RESTful; the list of resources that is returned should
be the last argument of the path.

Change-Id: I8b6a0713cf01a6c0107ca82fb35e99c42f0346a5
Related-Bug: 1421968

commit_message:
Avoid reloading policy files in policy.d for every call

We added policy files in policy.d, currently, the code will
reload the policy in policy.d every enforce been called.

This patch caches the file mtime of the most newest file in
the directory (or the directory itself if it is empty) and uses
that to detect if we need to reload files in the policy.d
directory.

Change-Id: I3ab1ce1f2132ea8672bf0765ee4b30ad126d4559
Closes-Bug: 1437992
Co-Authored-By: Eli Qiao <liyong.qiao@intel.com>
Cherry-pick: Ia8c273c8566a4b472cb8807b1576ef1dee8ef054

The comma is for log messages.  You need the % for translation.  So you can fix this where you can move variable in to the log(msg, var).

http://docs.openstack.org/developer/oslo.i18n/guidelines.html"}, {'account_id': 11865, 'date': '2015-04-08 01:27:42.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 2: Code-Review+1

So you should use % when the msg is used for both the LOG.error and exception thrown, or just for the exception thrown. [{'created': '2015-04-07 13:51:44.000000000', 'message': 'Fix log/error message formatting

Fix unresolved % placeholders in log/error messages.

Change-Id: Ib925014e79d2c380954d952f5dbc835971a0b320
Closes-Bug: #1439762
'}, {'created': '2015-04-07 19:45:16.000000000', 'message': 'Fix log/error message formatting

Fix unresolved % placeholders in log/error messages.

The following pattern used to log messages (or used for exception
messages) in the Manila code base,
msg = ("The number of %(bar)s found is %(quux)d that exceeds
       limit %(lim)d.", {"bar": "wooz", "quux": 14, "lim": 9})
LOG.error(msg)

results in undesired log messages, where the placeholders are not
substitued, as below,
ERROR <component> (u'The number of %(bar)s found is %(quux)d that
exceeds limit %(lim)d.', {'bar': 'wooz', 'quux': 14, limit: 9})

instead of the desired log message,
ERROR <component> The number of wooz found is 14 that exceeds limit 9.

Fix this erroneous format as below,
msg = ("The number of %(bar)s found is %(quux)d that exceeds
       limit %(lim)d." %  {"bar": "wooz", "quux": 14, "lim": 9})
LOG.error(msg)

Change-Id: Ib925014e79d2c380954d952f5dbc835971a0b320
Closes-Bug: #1439762
'}, {'created': '2015-04-08 05:09:04.000000000', 'message': "Fix log/error message formatting

- Use '%' for variable substitution in the message used for logging a
  call and throwing an exception.

- Use log marker functions(_LI(), _LW(), _LE(), and _LC()) to send
  message directly to the log.

- Use ',' for variable subsitution in the message in a log marker
  function.

Change-Id: Ib925014e79d2c380954d952f5dbc835971a0b320
Closes-Bug: #1439762
"}]
commit_message:
Fix log/error message formatting

- Use '%' for variable substitution in the message used for logging a
  call and throwing an exception.

- Use log marker functions(_LI(), _LW(), _LE(), and _LC()) to send
  message directly to the log.

- Use ',' for variable subsitution in the message in a log marker
  function.

Change-Id: Ib925014e79d2c380954d952f5dbc835971a0b320
Closes-Bug: #1439762

commit_message:
glusterfs_native: make {allow,deny}_access non-destructive

With this patch the allow_access and deny_access methods of
glusterfs_native will keep preexisting common names in the
affected GlusterFS volume 'auth.ssl-allow' option.

Also check in _setup_gluster_vol if 'auth.ssl-allow' is
set to a non-empty value to avoid semantically problematic
(and from Manila POV, useless) edge cases.

Change-Id: I952049d694509a338c7f56b45c5ef0872c3e7d70
Closes-Bug: #1439198

The tempest test test_add_list_remove_router_on_l3_agent could be failing because of a side-effect of this fix.
I believe distributed routers can be scheduled to an agent/node only if there are serviceable ports. 
Since prior to this change "get the ports on a subnet" erroneously returns all ports, an attempt to schedule a dvr on a node that doesn't really have serviceable ports could have succeeded. 
With this change, such an attempt would fail.
Suggest validate this hypothesis, if valid modify the test to add a port on subnet and host prior to adding the router to agent OR
 change the test to expect an exception in case of dvr.'}, {'account_id': 5209, 'date': '2015-02-11 21:57:22.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 3:

The code has nothing to do with the tempest test failure. As rajeev mentioned, it may be a side effect since the filter does not work for the "empty" subnet-id list and returing all the ports.
So when tempest test runs there might be some ports in there that are returned and it belongs to either compute, dhcp or lbaas this test would still pass.

Yes we need to fix the tempest to associated an interface to a router before assigining it to an agent for DVR. To make this test generic just add-interface ( subnet) and then assign it to agent.'}, {'account_id': 3, 'date': '2015-02-11 23:31:25.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 4: Verified+1

[{'created': '2015-02-09 23:23:07.000000000', 'message': 'Return from check_ports_exist_on_l3agent if no subnet found

The call to get_subnet_ids_on_router can return an empty list.
One such case is when doing a remove_router_interface.  If the
subnet_ids list is empty, the subsequent call to get the ports
on a subnet erroneously returns all ports.  In a large scale
environment, incorrectly looping through the entire list of ports
has been observed to cause significant performance problems
with remove_router_interface.  This change correctly returns
from check_ports_exist_on_l3agents immediately if no subnet is
found.

schedule_routers within notification is causing performance
problems for remove-router-interface.  schedule-routers doesn't
need to be called for remove-router-interface.  Moving
schedule_routers out to add_router_interface only.

commit_message:
Return from check_ports_exist_on_l3agent if no subnet found

The call to get_subnet_ids_on_router can return an empty list.
If the subnet_ids list is empty, the subsequent call to get
the ports on a subnet returns all ports.  If this occurs
when doing a remove_router_interface, the performance
of a remove_router_interface degrades significantly.  This change
returns immediately from check_ports_exist_on_l3agents if no
subnet is found.  A new unit test has been added to cover
the specific case of returning immediately without calling
get_ports when a remove_router_interface operation is performed.

Change-Id: I247d3bae152ab4f8ab7e00bd24d878eb08dca1ba
Closes-Bug: #1420032
Depends-On: I15bbf16fd4378c6431e9da8942d0968e7a012a91

commit_message:
Partial Revert "Removing ZFSSA driver"

This reverts commit c742566a6920f7260573fbd0dc71a5cc1e4a2311.

However, the ZFSSA iSCSI driver is still left out because there is no CI
for it.

Change-Id: Ibf830f295043624ca9a5dc90f1e3a897cb64915f

commit_message:
Make L3AgentSchedulerTestJSON DVR-aware

test_add_list_remove_router_on_l3_agent fails when testing with DVR
routers as distributed routers follow a different agent binding logic.

Due to this failure, performance improvements like e99f6e00 were reverted.
This called for a revision of the test case. This change ensures that,
when needed, the test provisions extra resources so that the binding logic
can be successful.

Closes-Bug: #1433349

Co-Authored-By: Armando Migliaccio <armamig@gmail.com>

Change-Id: I15bbf16fd4378c6431e9da8942d0968e7a012a91

commit_message:
Use gate64 cpu type during multinode testing

This relies on devstack to set up a working cpu map that
includes the gate64 cpu model.

Change-Id: I839e1c724821ba2624beddb5233eda24b50c149f
Depends-On: I00667713bfba67ab8cedbcb1660ff94d4f4bcc07

commit_message:
Add ipset element and hashsize tunables

Recently, these messages have been noticed in both tempest
logs, as well as reported by downstream users syslog:

  Set IPv4915d358d-2c5b-43b5-9862 is full, maxelem 65536 reached

So the default of 64K is not sufficient enough.

This change adds two config options to control both the number
of elements as well as the hashsize, since they should be
tuned together for best performance.  Slightly different
formats were required for 'ipset create' and 'ipset restore'.

The default values for these are now set to 131072 (maxelem) and
2048 (hashsize), which is an increase over their typical default values
of 65536/1024 (respectively), in order to fix the errors seen in
the tempest tests.

DocImpact

Change-Id: Ic0b5b38a840e737dc6be938230f4052974c8620f
Closes-bug: #1439817

commit_message:
Set template for docs

This change introduce conditional choice of template
for documentation.

When documentation is published to readthedocs.org default
readthedocs template is choosen, when documentation
will be published on docs.openstack.org default template for
Openstack Docs will be applied.

Change-Id: I8050fc423b3916b8a608d6a6e1ae7b2c613a16ba

commit_message:
Use secure default for bind interfaces

The bind interface defaulted to 0.0.0.0, or all interfaces.
Should only use secure defaults for config options, so default
to localhost-only.

SecImpact
Closes-Bug: 1424061

Change-Id: Ic111fd25f02d3b7a54f01ead5e75ed76fc8985ee

commit_message:
Improve docstrings for share and snapshot API methods

Modules 'manilaclient.v1.shares' and 'manilaclient.v1.share_snapshots' have
improper docstrings for various methods about expected parameters.
So, update them. Also make some improvements to handling of these parameters
that make various method consistent with each other about same parameters.
Add unit test coverage to updated methods.

Change-Id: I634de686f400b5df257c33e25c948ea509110e01
Closes-Bug: #1439690

commit_message:
Fix node_uuid option is required for port-create

A previous commit separated the -n/--node option from the --node_uuid
option on the "port-create" command. This meant that, even when the user
specified --node_uuid, the client required -n/--node as well and would
error out.

This moves these options onto a single CLI argument.

Change-Id: Idcc3217e07f9600f7db18182e9b1bc8b2ae356d3
Closes-bug: #1441374

commit_message:
python-ironicclient: Make src job voting, drop pxe_ssh job

The pxe_ssh job installs client from master and runs dsvm-tempest.
The src job installs the client from git (proposed patch) and runs
dsvm-tempest. This job has been running successfully without voting.
This makes it voting and drops the useless pxe_ssh job.

Change-Id: I6fb9e90328c55f79e2c85dd1e300f6eaff7f8ed8

commit_message:
Fix coverage so that it works for this repo

PBR provides test and testr entrypoints, the latter of which is not
recommended as its serviced directly by testr. Switch to test in
tox.ini and pass an option to PBR indicating the correct package
name to use when calling coverage. Also update .coveragerc with the
corrected source path, and stop omitting the tests themselves (after
all, tests should cover themselves!).

Change-Id: I04b1a5393979c5d82a794d35189743f688bdfdd8

(1 comment)

It will be difficult to use fakelibvirt with several contexts since all variables are globals, don't we have to think about something more modulable, like to pass these variables in the constructor?

Connection(..., _topology="...")'}, {'account_id': 8802, 'date': '2015-02-12 17:45:26.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 1:

(1 comment)

I was thinking about it.. not sure at the moment what is the right thing to do.

From the functional tests point of view, we are never calling Connect() directly and it would be very hard to pass topology in there.

I think there is another way to use the module in parallel, using the imp module, make a copy of the fake libvirt and replace the real libvirt with a copy in each instance of the compute service:

path =  os.path.dirname(os.path.realpath(fakelibvirt.__file__))
fake_obj = imp.find_module('fakelibvirt', [path])
self.fakelibvirt_mod = imp.load_module('fakelibvirt_mod', *fake_obj)

However, at the moment I don't think this is needed."}, {'account_id': 7730, 'date': '2015-02-13 11:53:05.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1:

What about to have these variables member of the class with a default values of the global variables. Then we can patch these attributes in the context of the object not the module for a test. What do you think?'}, {'account_id': 5511, 'date': '2015-02-13 12:16:02.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1: Code-Review-1

(1 comment)

I prefer what sahid says in the previous comment, this really is kind of moot.

I think it would actually be better to have them as instance variables that we can monkey patch so that they are contained to a specific test.'}, {'account_id': 2750, 'date': '2015-02-17 13:07:42.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 1:

Overall I like the direction of the patch series, however. There is value in the unit test fakelibvirt being simple. 

I'd actually propose making a functional test copy that could be more dynamic, because I think we don't want to possibly introduce bugs in the unit test side one when supporting more advanced functional test scenarios."}, {'account_id': 8802, 'date': '2015-03-16 16:15:08.000000000', 'content': 'Uploaded patch set 2.'}, {'account_id': 7730, 'date': '2015-03-16 16:39:56.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 2: Code-Review+1

commit_message:
libvirt: make fakelibvirt more customizable

Making capabilities XML to be dynamically formed using the module
default values, to allow the tests to modify it according to it's
needs

Change-Id: Id88711e7bf50d3ca704438a006bf549bd8f9791a

commit_message:
linuxbridge UT: Fix a regression of the recent ip_lib change

A recently merged change, I07d1d297f07857d216649cccf717896574aac301,
changed IPWrapper.get_devices to use /sys instead of executing ip command.
Unfortunately it broke linuxbridge unit tests, which seems to assume that
mocking utils.execute is enough in some places.  This commit fixes the
regression.

Closes-Bug: #1433417
Related-Bug: #1374663
Change-Id: I9570abe703b438a3fc358f747e25d023934d1ffd

commit_message:
Add maintenance check before call do_node_deploy

Currently if we set provision state to active or rebuild, there is
no maintenance check before signal to conductor, so add the check
on api side to save a rpc call.

Closes-Bug: #1441413
Change-Id: I2898b874b92f865d7e566fac0ede568d1b6c3831

commit_message:
Move variable initialization to prevent fail

It's possiable exception will not have details attribute.
In that case error message handling will fail.
This commit prevents this thereotic situation.

commit_message:
Add category management page

Implements blueprint enable-category-management
New table under 'Manage' section is added.

It allows to add new category and to delete category with no packages in it.

Depends-On: #170623
Change-Id: I10972db9f06ea77c6cb6c93c8bf379cc879a7bf5

commit_message:
Allow any admins to perform actions on packages

This prevents from the situation, when tenant is no longer exist
and there is no way to delete an application

Change-Id: I1539d0331634e8c665ff056f1bfde4de47880985
Closes-Bug: #1436618

Adds Cinder-VMDK role description

Since Fuel 6.1 supports Cinder-VMDK role,
this change should be reflected in User Guide.

Implements: blueprint cinder-vmdk-role

We have a hacking rule H105 (Don't use author tags) now
and the same policy has been applied to other neutron repos.

commit_message:
Renaming billing to rating

As CloudKitty is a rating and not a billing component, we needed to
rename all components and change paths on the API.
We've created a compatibility layer to help people with the migration.
The old API objects are now deprecated and shouldn't be used, they will
be removed in a near future.

Change-Id: I9e264f4ed01f4c94366eb51f612d634312b6a2f7

commit_message:
Update hacking to 0.10

Release notes:
http://git.openstack.org/cgit/openstack-dev/hacking/tag/?id=0.10.0

* Fix W292 (no newline at end of file)
* Fix H238 (old style class declaration, use new style)
* Skip H105 (Don't use author tags) temporarily.
* Remove H307 from ignore list since it is removed from Hacking rule.
* Remove H302 (import only modules) since there is no violation now.

commit_message:
Make secgroup rules more readable in security-group-show

Previously security_group_rules in security-group-show is
displayed in JSON dump in a format of one line per rule,
but each line is too long and hard to understand rules.
After this commit each rule is displayed as JSON dump with
indentation and we can easily read security group rules.

Partial-Bug: #1153766
Change-Id: I0a0d4afad340aee0346c73cf8881900375978858

commit_message:
Seggregates diagnostics in swift detection plugin

This patch seggregates individual diagnostics in swift detection
plugin. Earlier, all the diagnostics were combined and run as a
single command. This patch seggregates them into individual diagnostics
so thatreport of each of metric is available.

Change-Id: I23e099810838d7beee7e95035a172e32509a10b2
Closes-Bug: #1439508

Library: an io.murano.resources.NovaNetwork. It generates FloatingIP
assosiation resources if needed and returns a securityGroupName object
as one of the outputs of its joinInstance methods.

commit_message:
Nova Network support

Adds a support for Nova Network if Neutron is not present in the
current OpenStack deployment.

Supporting the Nova Network requires modifications in three different
parts of generated Heat Stack:
	1) Generated Security Groups and their rules should be of type
	   'AWS::EC2::SecurityGroup', not 'OS::Neutron::SecurityGroup'
	2) Security Group assignments should go to security_groups property
	   of Instance resource, not the network port (as port concept is
	   not present when using NovaNetwork)
	3) FloatingIP should be of type OS::Nova::FloatingIP and should be
	   associated with an Instance by OS::Nova::FloatingIPAssociation
	   resource.

To achieve p1 a SecurityGroupManager class of Core Library is made
abstract and is inherited by two concrete implementations:
NeutronSecurityGroupManager (containing the old MuranoPL code which
generated templates based on OS::Neutron::SecurityGroup) and a new
AwsSecurityGroupManager, which generates AWS-compliant firewall rules
which are consumed by NovaNetwork.

The particular concreate instance of this class is generated by the
default network of environment: Network class has got a new method called
generateSecurityGroupManager which returns an appropriate implementation.

For pp 2-3 a new inheritor of Network class has been added to the Core
Library: an io.murano.resources.NovaNetwork. It generates FloatingIP
association resources if needed and returns a securityGroupName object
as one of the outputs of its joinInstance methods.
The Instance class has been modified to properly handle these types of
outputs.
The instance of the NovaNetwork class is generated at the API side
when a new Environment is created and a is assigned to the
defaultNetworks.environment property of the environment if the neutron
is not defined in keystone.

Also this change moves the auth_utils module from engine to common, as
Keystone Client it contains is now used by the API process as well.

This changed is based on some of the code from the outdated changeset
I6f4b7908bd4bbcd375f64705c7dd06e3954f1ec7

Co-Authored-By: Alexander Tivelkov <ativelkov@mirantis.com>
Co-Authored-By: Stan Lagun <slagun@mirantis.com>

DocImpact

Change-Id: I4c48f33de100a5730ba1d086540d0d99e8fbf9b1
Implements-Blueprint: nova-network-support

commit_message:
Added handling of empty collections

Moved collector options directly in the module.
Added a nodata call in the rating processor which is called every
time the collection process retrieves no data from the backend.
It can be used to process some billing calculations even without
data.
Added a nodata call in the storage backend to handle the empty
collections more efficiently.

Change-Id: I37430823d2a5b416c9b171dfce75e136b9fa40df

commit_message:
Add L3 agent active/active options

The guide only provided an active/passive option for the L3 agent,
and this changed in the Juno release.

Closes-bug: #1372613

Change-Id: I5a8d4ef8440cb4fa3a1dfdad0a11a885e045ca43

commit_message:
Adopted cap.py in Icehouse

Copied cap.py script from Juno to Icehouse. Capped multiple libraries
based on pip freeze output generated from ceilometer py27 tox env.

The only difference between the autogenerated version of the file and
the one included in the patch is pymongo cap, which is lowered to avoid
pymongo 3.0+ that broke stable branches in addition to master.

Added pip freeze file for ceilometer unit tests for reference.

Related-Bug: #1441393
Change-Id: I742842c67576417a46eea52f10a74abd4d5b6656

commit_message:
tests/db: Add autospec=True to mocks

For the tests in ironic/tests/db/ add autospec=True to the mocks.

Using autospec=True helps to ensure that the mock object does not get
called with misspelled function names.

Change-Id: I8f66174c7f69fbb130acdaae50f4381c8152d0e3

commit_message:
Updating features documentation

This change updates the grammar and content of the features page.
Additionally it moves some of the more configuration related topics to
the configuration guides depending on the nature of the feature.

Change-Id: I1489ffbe1fe0f71a3a41a02e46614ab77263b8d8

commit_message:
Add Sahara log guideliness

During Kilo cycle we design and implement the new way of
creating logs in Sahara project. Now we add a document which
describe our vision on it.

Change-Id: I5f3c215600475a012d335d415fa826e1d4aa2cd8

commit_message:
Capped more global-requirements entries

Now used ceilometer pip-freeze output generated from py27 tox env.

The only difference between the autogenerated version of the file and
the one included in the patch is pymongo cap, which is lowered to avoid
pymongo 3.0+ that broke stable branches in addition to master.

Added pip freeze file for ceilometer unit tests for reference.

Related-Bug: #1441393
Change-Id: I742842c67576417a46eea52f10a74abd4d5b6656

commit_message:
Fix bug in playbooks/library/neutron

This change updates _add_router_interface to list ports for the router
device only, and not for all devices.  As we select specific device
ports only, we no longer need to skip over other device's ports, and
this indirectly fixes a bug where we were using 'next' instead of
'continue' to skip to the next iteration of the for loop.

Change-Id: I892dc0f58f1d8bbb7ebd46f7790c5420c4c8b94b
Closes-Bug: #1439295
(cherry picked from commit 8bd358d2c25f9bfb6011f751ef5342e012fbb6d8)

commit_message:
Fix rabbit OCF status check for reset_mnesia

In some conditions rabbit RA is unable to cleanup
mnesia because of the "reverse logic" bug in ocf
script, which is:

* It tries to check the status and rabbit is running
there
* But because of the reverse logic bug it didn't try
to kill rabbit
* That leads to "mnesia_unexpectedly_running" error.

Closes-Bug: #1441226

commit_message:
fix deployment serializer for cinder-vmware

There was checkbox "Cinder" on VMware tab which was removed. After it
corresponding changes should be done on deployment serializer.

Change-Id: I72dd52dbe07268b044987970c47776585e873ae4
Closes-bug: 1441577

commit_message:
UI fixes of Fuel registration flow

    - statistics settings are saved separately from tracking settings
    - removed duplicated code
    - removed fetching of remote login form
    - forms fields are disabled during requests
    - validation errors are reset when page opened

Closes-Bug:#1441099

Change-Id: Ie3130fa7b348072e07b1d59e258ba78e780e1dcc

commit_message:
Fix bug in playbooks/library/neutron

This change updates _add_router_interface to list ports for the router
device only, and not for all devices.  As we select specific device
ports only, we no longer need to skip over other device's ports, and
this indirectly fixes a bug where we were using 'next' instead of
'continue' to skip to the next iteration of the for loop.

Change-Id: I892dc0f58f1d8bbb7ebd46f7790c5420c4c8b94b
Closes-Bug: #1439295

commit_message:
Bump requirements in preparation for kilo

This commit brings o-a-d's requirements.txt in line w/
global-requirements.txt (master).  Also, we remove any packages that
are no longer required (a number were installed previously for tools
in scripts/ which no longer exist).  Additionally, we add some comments
indicating what requires a specific package.

NOTE: wheel requirement was originally added as pip < 6.0 required
wheels package in order to be able to install wheels themselves.  Since
we also bump pip to 6.0, wheel is no longer required.

Change-Id: I0de858283157cfb22db935bfe81a7ec23c9a7b9c
Closes-Bug: #1428106

commit_message:
Test instance connectivity in compute scenarios

Sets run_ssh to true in tempest.conf so compute scenarios attempt to ssh
to instances.

This will help distinguish instance connectivity faults from network faults.

Change-Id: Iaf76e430d82207116e97d18a5f15db23979354f5
Closes-bug: #1439756

revisions:
[{'created': '2015-04-08 04:03:36.000000000', 'message': 'Updated ansible to use the latest stable release

This change was made to improve ansible stability and speed.
Additionally this change comes with the now upstream lxc-container
module which will allow us to drop our carried module. In dropping
the module the entry point was changed from `lxc-container:` to
`lxc_contaner:`. All of the entry points have been changed in

commit_message:
Updated ansible to use the latest stable release

This change was made to improve ansible stability and speed.
Additionally this change comes with the now upstream lxc-container
module which will allow us to drop our carried module. In dropping
the module the entry point was changed from `lxc-container:` to
`lxc_container:`. All of the entry points have been changed in
support of the new upstream module and the carried `lxc-container`
module has been removed.

Partially Implements Blueprint: master-kilofication
Partial-Bug: 1399373

Change-Id: I4709eb78f153afc213225ea973570efa2e873993

commit_message:
Update Glance service to Kilo

To support a future release target deploying OpenStack Kilo release this
change applies the changes required to provide an updated role for
new deploys of Glance configured to run with the Kilo release.

Highlights:
- added template for glance-manage.conf
- changed api and registry paste.ini files to be templated
- added osprofiler filter to piplines in api and registry paste files

New user secrets:
- glance_profiler_hmac_key added for osprofiler use

New Tunables:
- glance_profiler_enabled for osprofiler use, default 'False'
- glance_http_keepalive for api and registry services, default 'True'
- glance_digest_algorithm for digital signatures, default 'SHA1'
- glance_task_executor for task execution, default 'taskflow'
- glance_policy_dirs & glance_policy_file for alternate policy config
sources, default 'policy.d' and 'policy.json' respectively
- glance_policy_default_rule for policy enforcement, default 'default'

Change-Id: I611a0ce3145861233c81c81084b1648b2b4b4423
Partially implements: blueprint master-kilofication

commit_message:
Remove Tempest NetworkBasicOps from commit tests

The NetworkBasicOps tests are failing most of the time, causing severe gate
check blockage and therefore hindering development progress.

The tests are being removed from the commit check in order to unblock the
gate, allowing development to continue while the root cause of this issue is
determined.

Change-Id: Iec35a592d04f1e2345207a0f8754c33ab1d4830e
Related-Bug: #1425255

commit_message:
Set containers to use the same apt repo as the host

This patch sets the AIO to use the same apt repository as the host in order to
reduce intermittent failures exhibited in environments other than RAX Cloud.

Change-Id: Id4069efa51f6198504d0eb1cfcd9c8beb9607075
Closes-Bug: #1441148

commit_message:
Restart apache2 after local_settings.py is changed

This change ensures that apache2 is restarted after the horizon
configuration is changed.

Closes-Bug: #1441110
Change-Id: I7713995b1fa91e42b27a28856cdf21814c037b6f

Updated Ironic Microversions Spec to fix minor errors.

commit_message:
Do not use sudo to cleanup the temporary directory

81d2ab1fd1cf4c3f8c5e7feea6cb836cde33baa0 required sudo to cleanup the
temporary directory, as it still had the image cache.
After 03c5b6bd09cbf81b9872f68ec0ef43ea01c1ecda, disk-image-create uses
its default cache (in ~), so there is no more need for sudo when
removing the temporary directory.

Change-Id: I081a462ea0b5f8008ffdd7a5abbe1d35da87059c

commit_message:
Add links to third-party components licenses

We need to provide links to licenses of deb packages, rpm packages
and javascript libraries inluded in MOS iso. Generating and publishing
pdf files with license reports is a part of a process which can't
be included in fuel-docs make system, so only links to the files are
provided.

Related-Bug: #1440131
Change-Id: I3fe295aeb97a4007244658840ed6d87f171f4307
(cherry picked from commit e063e71a972aa8bbb6645d25565a2d4162f2c1ad)

commit_message:
glusterfs_native: negotiate volumes with glusterd

So far glusterfs_native was able to create shares
from volumes listed in 'glusterfs_targets' config
option.

New behavior: a regexp pattern is to be provided
through the glusterfs_volume_pattern config option.
Upon share creation, grep gluster server's volumes
with this pattern and create the new share from
one among those.

Change-Id: I12ba0dbad0b1174c57e94acd5e7f6653f5bfaae8
Closes-Bug: #1437176

If some driver starts using "manage" change and this driver starts failing, due to this specific change, then you won't be able just to revert this change not breaking another driver. 

Also in normal situations there can be concurrent change in other driver that needs small "manager" change and it is tied to this big driver change.

There is no real reason to keep two different things combined. Just merge two comimts instead of one. Is it a problem?'}, {'account_id': 2417, 'date': '2015-04-04 18:03:43.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 1:

The main reason to NOT split this up is that it's extra work and it will take longer. I'm not against spending the extra time though if there is a good reason.

I'm still confused about the risk of submitting this bugfix in 1 patch though. The only change to the manager is to copy an additional key/value from one dictionary to another. This can't cause anything bad to happen so far as I can see.

If we break this into 2 changes then the driver change still depends on the manager change, and you can't back out one without backing out the other (the netapp driver would start breaking if we backed out the manager change and left the netapp driver change in)."}, {'account_id': 11865, 'date': '2015-04-05 03:48:41.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1: Code-Review-1

revisions:
[{'created': '2015-04-03 20:42:04.000000000', 'message': 'Prevent share servers from being created with unsupported network types

The segmentation approach used by the network plugin associated with a share
server was not declared to the driver. This made it impossible for a driver
to know whether a network used VLAN, GRE, VXLAN, or any other segmentation
approach, and introduced the possibility of an incorrect segmentation
approach to be applied to a share server.
This patchset provides the network type to the driver, and applies a correct
filter to the Data ONTAP driver for supported technologies with a clean error
message.

Closes-bug: 1438825

Change-Id: I9f20a26e9c10d49ca3c82a46f49bdb5c65fd4a24
'}, {'created': '2015-04-07 16:32:54.000000000', 'message': 'Prevent share servers from being created with unsupported network types

The segmentation approach used by the network plugin associated with a share
server was not declared to the driver. This made it impossible for a driver
to know whether a network used VLAN, GRE, VXLAN, or any other segmentation
approach, and introduced the possibility of an incorrect segmentation
approach to be applied to a share server.
This patchset provides the network type to the driver, and applies a correct
filter to the Network Manager for supported technologies with a clean error

commit_message:
Add segmentation ID checks for different segmentation types

The segmentation approach used by the network plugin associated with a share
server was not declared to the driver. This made it impossible for a driver
to know whether a network used VLAN, GRE, VXLAN, or any other segmentation
approach, and introduced the possibility of an incorrect segmentation
approach to be applied to a share server.
This patchset makes the network_type field available to the driver, and
checks that segmentation id has valid values for different network_types.
If the segmentation id has an incorrect value, it fails with a clean
error message.

Partial-Bug: 1438825

Change-Id: I9f20a26e9c10d49ca3c82a46f49bdb5c65fd4a24

This spec proposes a new power driver which does reboot of a node
via SSH access. OS Reboot driver intended for hardware without
out-of-band power control.

commit_message:
Add links to third-party components licenses

We need to provide links to licenses of deb packages, rpm packages
and javascript libraries inluded in MOS iso. Generating and publishing
pdf files with license reports is a part of a process which can't
be included in fuel-docs make system, so only links to the files are
provided.

Related-Bug: #1440131
Change-Id: I3fe295aeb97a4007244658840ed6d87f171f4307

commit_message:
Fixed NotificationTransformer to handle missing InstanceServiceStatus

Fixed NotificationTransformer to not send exists notifications for
new Trove instances which do not have an InstanceServiceStatus
created for them yet. The notifications for these instances will
eventually be sent during the next iteration of the scheduled task.

Change-Id: I002ab89f8c7715310f1890a34967c8172a5d96ef

commit_message:
Option to install Fedora LT kernel is added back

Migration is not needed as orchestrator serializer code supports
both options (VLAN splinters for 6.0 and Fedora kernel for 6.1).

Closes-Bug: #1439821
Change-Id: I8d266d85494dd733620bb8ae9c8afe8bd75a20bb

commit_message:
Shotgun will always try to save stdout and stderr

Added CCStringIO - "carbon copy" StringIO which in addition
to normal behavior can pass any write to different file-like
object.
It is used as a stdout for executing commands via fabric
and when errors occur during command execution it is used as a source
of stdout. In addition it also proxies everything to
regular sys.stdout.
Removed capturing of stderr for fabric's "run" since
it is always in stdout in our case

Change-Id: I022128141ed142561213a9633bc0fe0f8ccc2685
Closes-Bug: #1434574

commit_message:
Respect format when printing Fuel's VERSION

* Used Serializer when printing VERSION
* Format flags are now a mutually exclusive
* Format is now stored in one parser attribute - before it was
  one boolean attribute per format
* APIClient.get_fuel_version() now returns Python dict instead of
  formatted YAML
* added 'consts' file

Change-Id: I3861dc34aa2838712408bd715e3af48762b9fd9b
Closes-Bug: #1411661

commit_message:
Upgrade images context

1. allow to create images without location. it needs for creating
hundreds of fake images to test performance of list-like functions.
2. added size property for image creation
3. implemented TODO in cleanup of images context

Change-Id: Ib4c35f8fa422c5080f06941bb41aed3becccb837

[{'created': '2015-03-31 10:39:41.000000000', 'message': 'Fix incorrect statement in inline neutronv2 docs

The function doc header for network/neutron/v2/api.py _create_port()
states that it accepts an optional set of MAC addresses to use.

However, it only uses one, which is selected by pop().

This commit merely changes the doc string to indicate that the function
operates on only a single MAC address, not on the whole set.

Change-Id: I0fc845572836b6a6773cc7beaeefd7b0d1cfd5e7
Related-bug: #1405131
'}]
commit_message:
Fix incorrect statement in inline neutronv2 docs

The function doc header for network/neutron/v2/api.py _create_port()
states that it accepts an optional set of MAC addresses to use.

However, it only uses one, which is selected by pop().

This commit merely changes the doc string to indicate that the function
operates on only a single MAC address, not on the whole set.

Change-Id: I0fc845572836b6a6773cc7beaeefd7b0d1cfd5e7
Related-bug: #1405131

commit_message:
Closing Upload Package from reloads package list

Before one could upload a package and click cancel on second or
third step and list of apps would not be updated.

Change-Id: I78a10b21d1f2506b075cd3b6cd0e83ef07e036ec
Closes-Bug: #1438756

commit_message:
Policy enforcement 'services' relationship

Following changes were made in congress mapping of murano objects:
Relationship "services" is created for environment and its applications.
Property tenant_id on environment is no longer needed.
Ownerships respect embedded objects within the tree.

Change-Id: I846d4d2be9ebf2fd7d5b75ea8e36eed87e56a633
Closes-Bug: #1439591

[{'created': '2015-04-08 06:36:53.000000000', 'message': "Don't touch the sqla orm object

Updating the orm object to ensure that the returned type
is a UUID object triggers a UPDATE call to the DBMS without
transaction.

This change fixes the rest API instead of allowing text and uuid.UUID
type in the driver.

Change-Id: I464f7cedfe171f8d755e187b5bccff3535408641
"}]
commit_message:
Don't touch the sqla orm object

Updating the orm object to ensure that the returned type
is a UUID object triggers a UPDATE call to the DBMS without
transaction.

This change fixes the rest API instead of allowing text and uuid.UUID
type in the driver.

Change-Id: I464f7cedfe171f8d755e187b5bccff3535408641

commit_message:
Work with pymongo 3.0

pymongo 3.0 renamed mongos_enum to read_pref_mode_from_name which
was causing the unit tests to fail.

Change-Id: Iaa7fd7221c2e6c865633ef342e6b83304a1de655
Closes-Bug: 1441393

commit_message:
VPNaaS: Remove check for bash usage

Like Neutron, removing the check for bash script usage and
changed bash scripts to use '#!/usr/bin/env bash'.

Change-Id: Iab8ce0382695be8d8c7cd644b036dbf41dfd90b3
Closes-Bug: #1441244

commit_message:
Improve dos.py for manual manipulation with environment

Added new actions to dos.py:
   create               Create new environment
   slave-add            Add node to env
   slave-change         Change node vcpu and memory
   slave-remove         Remove node from environment
   admin-setup          Setup admin node
   node-start           Start a node
   node-destroy         Destroy a node
   node-reset           Restart a node

Change-Id: I6a5ff908f316c3fabca53200ccf29476565d892a
Blueprint: fuel-devops-manual-env-manipulation

commit_message:
Quota update fix when calculating settable quotas for unlimited range

This patch implements the case when updating quotas and current settable
range is unlimited (min:-1, max:-1).
Current implementation of math operations between quota values moved
into a new class for that specific purpouse.

Changes:
- New test that to cover this new case.
- Updated test cases to support the fix.
- New class that handles unlimited values when performing math
operations between quota values.
- Fix for unlimited range calculation
- Improvement for quota limit validation

Closes-Bug: #1306229
Co-Authored-By: Sergio Cazzolato <sergio.j.cazzolato@intel.com>

Change-Id: I197d8d3adac9203aa6263cfca22fe91fa525f9d6

commit_message:
Fix test_cannot_change_repos_on_operational_env

Since the patch Ief7cb7440db02ecbc0dd42a2cb05b8f66b83e7a0 the default
priority value for CentOS's MOS repo was changes to 'None', and the
other patch I0c58a03b2cd83e1fb196f5a55002d5a869277c6f didn't know
nothing about it. Parallel merging of them led to broken test.

This patch fix test to fit new criteria.

Change-Id: I0e2d2d280f85e19bc73dfc08cab407733e7f3dc2
Closes-Bug: #1441509

commit_message:
Json exporters for stats added

For system tests purposes http handlers for fetching stats
added into analytics.
Implemented OSWLs exporters:
- /api/v1/json/oswls/<master_node_uid>,
- /api/v1/json/oswls/<master_node_uid>/<resource_type>
Implemented installation info exporter:
- /api/v1/json/installation_info/<master_node_uid>
Implemented action logs exporter:
- /api/v1/json/action_logs/<master_node_uid>

Change-Id: I746b43c387c90b20c70d5160d92859b4b44998c1
Closes-Bug: #1438228

commit_message:
Heat config changes for kilo

This commit does the following:

- refreshes files/environment.d/default.yaml and
  files/templates/AWS_CloudWatch_Alarm.yaml from kilo
- adds heat_max_nested_stack_depth and heat_trusts_delegated_roles
  variables (the default values of the config options these variables
  represent changed between juno and kilo and we now default to the
  kilo values while giving operators the ability to upgrade to kilo
  with the juno values)
- adds heat_profiler_hmac_key, heat_profiler_enabled, and
  heat_profiler_trace_sqlalchemy variables which control the enablement of
  osprofiler
- removes unneeded [clients_*] sections from templates/heat.conf.j2
- renames heat_clients_endpoint variable to heat_clients_endpoint
- adds heat_clients_heat_endpoint so we can set [clients_heat] to use
  externalURL rather than internalURL

Partially implements blueprint: master-kilofication

Change-Id: If445d2ad394539a13fece656cb4089b042df542a

The fix looks fine, but it would be better if you could add a hacking rule to catch and prevent this in the future.  See https://github.com/openstack/nova/blob/master/nova/hacking/checks.py#L341 as an example.'}, {'account_id': 1207, 'date': '2015-03-16 14:43:09.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 1:

Thang: I'm not sure how those hacking checks would catch this type of error. The basic cases are all caught, there cases are where the msg is declared on a different line to where it is used. You'd need to do full static analysis (find all variables passed as the first arg to LOG.{info|warning|error| exception}, track if they are passed to any other function (many are passed to raise() for example and should therefore be _()), and if not report an error) to catch these, which is not trivial. I'd love to see it, but it is a big piece of work."}, {'account_id': 1207, 'date': '2015-03-16 14:43:18.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1: Code-Review+2'}, {'account_id': 8247, 'date': '2015-03-16 14:51:52.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1: Code-Review+1

(154 comments)

I had been thinking of doing this myself. I think a lot of the confusion we have had around proper logging has been due to a lot of examples in the existing codebase that are not following the guidelines. Thanks for doing this.

That said, if we are going to do a patch to clean up these errors, there are a lot of instances you have missed. Additional cleanup needed before this is ready.

The hacking checks that nova has is interesting. It certainly can't catch all instances, as Duncan has pointed out. But it looks like with what they have they would at least catch the blatantly obvious ones of the format LOG.error("No marker"). That has some value in my opinion.

I'm OK if that is not addressed with this patch, but I do think it is something we should consider to help reduce the number of incorrect cases.'}, {'account_id': 9535, 'date': '2015-03-16 18:08:41.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1: Code-Review-1

(1 comment)

I disagree with Sean on changes related to delayed string interpolation, but agree with him on his comments where he points out instances where marker functions have not been changed.'}, {'account_id': 5997, 'date': '2015-03-16 20:14:13.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1: Code-Review-1

If you are making changes to cinder/brick/* please submit a patch against the os-brick project with the same changes please.'}, {'account_id': 11904, 'date': '2015-03-16 21:07:11.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 1:

The problem with some of the cases of not doing the delayed string interpolation is some of them could actually cause an exception with the way they are done. The safest option is to pass the formatting arguments into the LOG call. This isn't just to delay the string formatting."}, {'account_id': 8247, 'date': '2015-03-16 21:11:49.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1: -Code-Review

+1 to what Sean said. If we have some kind of standard, like every LOG.info|warn|error must have _LI|LW|LE follow it, then the hacking check would be very simple to do and we would be able to catch most of these errors.'}, {'account_id': 9535, 'date': '2015-03-17 09:38:53.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 1:

I didn't mean that we shouldn't do it, I just meant that as far as the LP bug is concerned this fixes it (as soon as changes to pending _ are done) and as such should not be voted -1 for that.
For the other changes we could do a follow-up patch with them, or if Ankit doesn't mind they can be done here. I'm cool with both options."}, {'account_id': 11904, 'date': '2015-03-17 09:41:29.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1:

Ah, got it. Thanks Gorka. I would like to see it done here, but if it is decided not to then I agree we can do so in a follow up patch.'}, {'account_id': 10485, 'date': '2015-03-17 10:07:15.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1:

commit_message:
Fix missing translations for log messages

Fixed log translations for error, info and warning messages with
appropriate marker function according to the marker function
standards [1].

As LOG.warn has deprecated [2] so I have changed LOG.warn to
LOG.warning.

[1] http://docs.openstack.org/developer/oslo.i18n/guidelines.html#choosing-a-marker-function
[2] http://bugs.python.org/issue13235

Closes-Bug: 1431256
Change-Id: I6f1b5b6d80cc7b38d5a99fb74aa78298ecad7edc

commit_message:
Validate required parameters for token-based authentication

Currently user can specify only 'input_auth_token' parameter
and get attribute error in the client. To fix this issue we should
validate that user provides both arguments: 'input_auth_token'
and 'service_catalog_url'.

Change-Id: Ie783f1d7e091138671c54be899ca84c6a28c9f9b
Closes-Bug: #1439683

Thanks for this, its great to have more coverage of the validators, However I think the tests should be re-worked to remove the CSR parsing elements entirely and instead use a mock. These unit tests should try to be as explicit as possible in what they are testing, but in this case if one fails I would not be able to tell if the fault lies in the CSR parser or in the logic of the validator without deeper investigation. commit_message:
Don't set repo priority on CentOS if not specified

We shouldn't set repo priority on CentOS if it's not specified, because
we want base mirror to be resolved with yum defaults.

Change-Id: Ief7cb7440db02ecbc0dd42a2cb05b8f66b83e7a0
Related-To: blueprint consume-external-ubuntu

[{'created': '2015-03-26 13:51:04.000000000', 'message': 'Add posibility to filter nested attributes for collected ones

For some oswl resources their attributes contains nested ones (e.g.
"attachments" attribute for "volume" resource is list of dicts which
elements contain info about particular attachment point to server). But
nor all inner atribute should be collected by different reasons. To
support  filtering of resulting set of inner attributes
"resource_description" dict was changed and corresponding processing
logic was added to statistic.utils module.

Change-Id: Ifbfa4d7be78372aeb2015fd6b5dbefefbc9e9e52
Closes-Bug: #1436190
'}]
commit_message:
Add posibility to filter nested attributes for collected ones

For some oswl resources their attributes contains nested ones (e.g.
"attachments" attribute for "volume" resource is list of dicts which
elements contain info about particular attachment point to server). But
nor all inner atribute should be collected by different reasons. To
support  filtering of resulting set of inner attributes
"resource_description" dict was changed and corresponding processing
logic was added to statistic.utils module.

Change-Id: Ifbfa4d7be78372aeb2015fd6b5dbefefbc9e9e52
Closes-Bug: #1436190

commit_message:
Add 'always_editable' attribute to repo_setup

Despite the fact that repos are part of cluster attributes and we can't
change cluster attributes after deployment, we have to be able to change
repos list. It makes sense, because for instance, user wants to add new
nodes but his mirrors were moved to another server, so current repos
are unavailable.

This patch adds support of the 'always_editable' flag in openstack.yaml.
With that flag we can mark attribute groups to be available for editing
after deployment.

Related-To: blueprint consume-external-ubuntu
Change-Id: I0c58a03b2cd83e1fb196f5a55002d5a869277c6f

commit_message:
Add possibility to change repos on deployed envs

Despite the fact that repos are part of cluster attributes and we can't
change cluster attributes after deployment, we have to be able to change
repos list. It makes sense, because for instance, user wants to add new
nodes but his mirrors were moved to another server, so current repos
are unavailable.

Implements: blueprint consume-external-ubuntu
Change-Id: Ic1a3b721572397f2ee3b030934018fe940b91370

commit_message:
Fix intermittent UT failures in test_utils

Change eba4c2941ee introduced these tests. However they are not that useful as they
simply mimick the code, without really ensuring that the behavior is expected, so
they provide negative value ([1]), plus, they fail randomly.

This patch removes them in favor of a more useful functional check.

[1] http://googletesting.blogspot.com/2015/01/testing-on-toilet-change-detector-tests.html

Closes-bug: #1441347

Change-Id: I8a321995295deef7f6d30be303486be491e2771f

commit_message:
Add context.update_store in the task entry functions

When a new task is spawned in conductor and compute,
context.update_store() is not called in the newly created
task because of which the context information is not added
in the logs.

This patch adds context.update_store() in the task functions
 -_do_build_and_run_instance() of compute manager
 - build_instance(), rebuild_instance() and
   unshelve_instance() of conductor manager.

Change-Id: Ie7406c05a0022f49830a611946bde95a123943f6
Closes-bug: #1404268

Remove old script for graph checks

After enabling new CI job for validating graph and removing
old one, we could remove old tests configuration and runner.

Change-Id: I51f82bae601e9fe9999af62cc40a4dbbe00a3f61

commit_message:
Enable file injection in nova.conf

In Juno by default file injection is disabled,
so that we can not boot instance with user personality

Change-Id: I6dce3f8177cbdc6a75d58b4a748687afdf57c040
Closes-Bug: #1440817

commit_message:
Wait for ready 'nailgun' container

Add property 'is_container_ready' and method
'wait_for_ready_container()' to BaseActions class.

Add wait for 'nailgun' container.

Closes-Bug: #1441247

commit_message:
Get project name from setup.cfg in install_venv.py

We hard code project name with OpenStack in install_venv.py now,
It would be better use specific project name like cinder did.
This commit extract the project name from setup.cfg

Change-Id: I40370fe3141eb08647d7d3b8f629f09783055369

[{'created': '2015-03-09 05:45:01.000000000', 'message': 'Provide a generic auth plugin loader

For keystonemiddleware, shade and other projects that do more
complicated option loading than simply CLI or CONF file provide a means
to load an auth plugin where options are discovered by a provided
function.

This plugin is designed to work with the options as provided by
get_options rather than either the argparse or CONF registration
functions.

Use these as the default loading mechanism for the existing argparse and
CONF functions as it standardizes the mechanism between the two sources.

Change-Id: I15634ac30581c7aea14e709f12fb202570190f46
Closes-Bug: #1428900

commit_message:
Provide a generic auth plugin loader

For keystonemiddleware, shade and other projects that do more
complicated option loading than simply CLI or CONF file provide a means
to load an auth plugin where options are discovered by a provided
function.

This plugin is designed to work with the options as provided by
get_options rather than either the argparse or CONF registration
functions.

Use these as the default loading mechanism for the existing argparse and
CONF functions as it standardizes the mechanism between the two sources.

Change-Id: I15634ac30581c7aea14e709f12fb202570190f46
Closes-Bug: #1428900

commit_message:
Add glance support in magnum.

List of changes:
1. Added glanceclient implementation in magnum client.
2. Added testcases for glanceclient integration.

Change-Id: Ia6f46d61cbc1031b66e6f725b693a12071639a37
Implements: blueprint add-glance-image-properties-support

commit_message:
Support fwaasrouterinsertion extension

fwaasrouterinsertion extension allows to specify which routers implement
a firewall (on create/update). This changes adds its support by allowing
to:
* set routers with --router option in firewall-create/update commands,
* unset routers with --no-routers option in firewall-update command.

Change-Id: I654c1ddd4140a60b8a09237f7142ad211e951d92
Closes-Bug: #1435264

commit_message:
Update links in Community Support Appendix

guides.

Remove API links, they are all now on developer.openstack.org - and the
first link in the section contains all documents, so we do not need to
duplicate the information here.

Remove tests from HA routers test framework

was running an additional 9 tests that should not have been run.

commit_message:
change s3 endpoint from nova to ec2-api for devstack

fix register_image function -
code can access outer variable but "set operation" will create
a new name in the current scope, which cover the outer one.

Change-Id: Ica2750fbf05e0d3c68ed199996afd8c6e7662229

commit_message:
libvirt: remove unnecessary flavor parameter

The instance now has the flavor as part of the object. There is
no reason to pass this to:
 - _get_guest_config_meta
 - _get_guest_xml

The unit test test_get_guest_config was also updated. The flavor in
the test has 3 disks and these need to be validated correctly.

Change-Id: I1170aefcd4912e091f4b85e91d351b4372522fa9

commit_message:
Fix resources allocation in documentation

Allocation of contributed resources generates
incorrectly, so this patch fixes res allocation.
Now contributed resources are in Contributed Heat
Resource Types page and integrated are in OpenStack
Resource Types page. Escaping from using env because
of all_resources loaded from PluginMapping.

Change-Id: I6d7c501f231c546f909c3ed7f19fc8d1fc04e927
Closes-bug: #1433675

http://logs.openstack.org/30/167830/14/experimental/check-tempest-dsvm-neutron-full-non-isolated/1897ebc/console.html'}, {'account_id': 1921, 'date': '2015-04-02 10:29:53.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 14:

I think the non-isolated neutron job has been broken by 9ce97dfa353e3659aa0ec0a7f62ed3a7e54c4bdf, not by this one.

The logic there is the following:
- if tenant isolation if off, do not use the credential provider network
- try to see if we can use fixed_network_name
- if admin is available, get an admin network client, and list fixed_network_name, get its uuid
- start the server with that uuid

Now, the problem is that in our n-net devstack fixed_network_name is visible to all tenants, but in neutron it isn't (it's not a shared network), it's just a network visible to demo user.

Which is ok for most tests, but not for those using force_tenant_isolation, as they will get a dedicate tenant, which cannot access fixed_network_name.

The underlying issue is - in my opinion - that n-net API does not behave correctly, as it does not show the fixed_network_name network to tenants, only to admins. So we are forced to use admin to verify if fixed_network_name do exist.

But there is also an issue in tempest, which is we do not take in account the force_tenant_isolation setting in fixed_networks, and also the compute admin quota test does not request a network / subnet to be created.

And when we create a network client to verify the network, we should use an admin one only if neutron is not available.

I will prepare a separate patch to solve these issues."}, {'account_id': 1921, 'date': '2015-04-02 10:43:29.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 14:

commit_message:
Embed network resoruces and credentials in TestResources

Define a new class TestResources which embeds credentials and
their network resources.
This makes it easier to obtain network resources for a set
of credentials in case of preprovisioned accounts.

Partially-implements: bp test-accounts-continued

Change-Id: Ie3d5e2471db7371e1109fd24a716e7c449843904

commit_message:
Skip test_security_groups_basic_ops for vnic_type=direct of macvtap

Currently there is no security groups support for SR-IOV in openstack.
So test_security_groups_basic_ops should be skipped when
using vnic_type=direct or vnic_type=macvtap.

Closes-Bug: 1437799
Change-Id: If0d40730f057dfb2d73c246b2104b5be2e4c503e

commit_message:
Fix security group checking action permissions raise error

The security group usage did not contain key 'available'
when using nova-network, so it must be checked before using.

Change-Id: I1a4b78360ce84731449ca9416c36c552e35fe20b
Closes-Bug: #1422049

commit_message:
Adds rpc_ping method to new datastores

Newly implemented datastores
 - couchdb
 - db2
 - vertica
were missing on a new API, rpc_ping, method in their managers.

This patchset adds rpc_ping to these managers and also their
complimentary unit-tests to their respective managers' test files.

Change-Id: I080804efdb25726df0a3ff431e2f73f9b1f5be3d
Closes-Bug: 1439963
